==Old English==
===Etymology===
Apparently named from the goddess [[Eastre|Ēastre]], from a suffixed form of Indo-European ''*āus-'' ‘dawn’.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[asteron|āsteron]], Old High German [[ostarun|ōstarūn]] (German [[Ostern]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'æ:astre/

===Noun===
'''ēastre''' ''n''
# [[Easter]]

